t: To the chief Musician upon Jonath–elem–rechokim, Michtam of David, when the Philistines took him in Gath.
Be*p merciful unto me, O God: for man would swallow me up; he fighting daily oppresseth me.
Mine*p enemies would daily swallow me up: for they be many that fight against me, O thou most High.
What*p time I am afraid, I will trust in thee.
In*p God I will praise his word, in God I have put my trust; I will not fear what flesh can do unto me.
Every*p day they wrest my words: all their thoughts are against me for evil.
They*p gather themselves together, they hide themselves, they mark my steps, when they wait for my soul.
Shall*p they escape by iniquity? in thine anger cast down the people, O God.
Thou*p tellest my wanderings: put thou my tears into thy bottle: are they not in thy book?
When*p I cry unto thee, then shall mine enemies turn back: this I know; for God is for me.
In*p God will I praise his word: in the Lord*s will I praise his word.
In*p God have I put my trust: I will not be afraid what man can do unto me.
Thy*p vows are upon me, O God: I will render praises unto thee.
For*p thou hast delivered my soul from death: wilt not thou deliver my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living?
